properties.Title: Fog Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Near zero visibility in fog is expected or occurring over some areas. Areas of fog will begin to clear from west to east starting overnight. Patchy fog may persist into Monday night for regions of east-central Alberta. Freezing drizzle will also be possible tonight, especially in regions near the Saskatchewan border. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility in some locations. Fog advisories are issued when near zero visibilities in fog are expected or occurring. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ABstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ABStorm.
